summary: Fixed two critical bugs in the Beauty Booking module JavaScript files. Bug 1: Fixed Fetch API response body being consumed multiple times by reading the response body once before calling showFetchError() and passing the pre-parsed errorData to avoid double-read errors. Updated showFetchError() to accept optional errorData parameter. Fixed in beauty-booking.js (lines 39-58, 370-400) and beauty-calendar.js (lines 104-114). Bug 2: Fixed translate() function in beauty-booking.js to return null instead of the translation key when translation is not found, allowing fallback text to display correctly. The function now returns null when window.Laravel.translations[key] is undefined, enabling the || 'fallback' pattern to work as expected.
current_status: Both bugs verified and fixed. Fetch API error handling now correctly reads response body only once, preventing 'body stream already read' errors. Translation function now returns falsy values when translations are missing, allowing fallback messages to display properly. All JavaScript files updated and linted with no errors. Ready for testing.
